ces bacon, cut in half (3 short pieces per burger)","3 ½ oz Roma tomatoes, sliced (approx. 2 md. tomatoes)","4 - 8 pieces butter lettuce","4 burger buns, toasted"]}],"id":"r175475","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-TZyzcImWY5k\/XZQwNoA3MrI\/AAAAAAAAcj8\/gYYAbeuZ3MYm4FpON1oKN1HwXiRWtdvmACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_VgHyBuK12va3escg.png","title":"Turkey, Bacon and Avocado Burgers","publishedAt":"2017-06-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"35 g","fat":"25 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"682 g","calories":"2142 kJ \/ 512 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling wrap, grill, thermometer, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Suggested internal cooking temperature for turkey is 165°F.","Ground turkey can be replaced with turkey meat. To grind turkey meat: place a zip lock bag onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in 4 oz turkey breast and 4 oz of turkey thighs, cut into 1 inch pieces. Repeat with a second zip lock bag, 4 oz turkey breast and 4 oz turkey thighs, cut into 1 inch pieces.  Place both bags in freezer until partially frozen (approx. 1 hr.). Place 1 zip lock bag of frozen turkey meat into mixing bowl after chopping onions and grind <strong>6 sec\/speed 6<\/strong>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Place bag of remaining frozen turkey into mixing bowl and grind <strong>6 sec\/speed 6<\/strong>. Add reserved ground turkey meat and Turbo <strong>1 sec\/3 times<\/strong>. Use spatula to evenly combine before proceeding with recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","50m","2h","4 portions"]}